Describe a sports competition you watched

I would like to talk about the final match of the 33rd SEA Games between Vietnam and Thailand, which was one of the most thrilling sports events I've ever watched.
It took place just a few months ago, so the memories are still very fresh in my mind. On that day, my family and I gathered around the TV to watch the match together, and it turned out to be an emotional roller coaster from start to finish.
In the first half, Thailand dominated the game and managed to score two early goals. At that point, many Vietnamese fans, including myself, were convinced that we were heading towards a disappointing defeat. It was honestly quite difficult to stay optimistic.
However, the second half was a completely different story. Vietnam made an incredible comeback by scoring scoring two equalizing goals, and then, in extra time, our striker netted the winning goal. The moment was absolutely electrifying, and I remember jumping up in excitement along with my family.
What made the victory even more special was the long-standing rivalry between Vietnam and Thailand. Defeating such a strong opponent made the win even more satisfying. After the match, the streets were filled with people celebrating, waving flags, and honking horns. It truly felt like the entire nation was united in joy.
What I admire most about this match is the players' determination and never-give-up spirit. Despite being two goals down, they showed incredible resilience and managed to turn the game around.
Overall, it was an unforgettable experience, and even now, thinking about it makes me feel extremely proud and emotional
